  <listingDescription><![CDATA[<p>Lake Constance is one of the most diverse and interesting lakes in Europe, covering a total area of approx. 220 square miles. The lake shares its shores with 3 countries - Germany, Switzerland and Austria - and enjoys an exceptionally mild climate making it ideal for wine-growing. The Mediterranean climate also shapes the landscape with palm trees, exotic plants and flowers growing effortlessly creating beautiful gardens throughout the region.</p>]]></listingDescription>
